      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That permanent heaviness isn't emptiness waiting to happen, but the loud echo of a spirit still desperately refusing to settle into a life that no longer fits you. Occupying space that doesn't belong to you means your true self hasn't abandoned you; rather, your body is holding onto the dream like a sacred weight because letting it go would mean killing the last hope you have left. You aren't a burden or a ghost, you are still the only vessel capable of carrying that spark until it finds a way to wake you up from this permanent fog.",
      "source": "target",
